        <updateDate>2017-05-23T17:06:05Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Safeguarding America's Armed Forces and Effectiveness Act or the SAAFE Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal judicial code to limit civil claims against a foreign state for injuries, death, or damage that occurs inside the United States as a result of an act of international terrorism or a tortious act. Specifically, it limits such claims to only those for injuries, death, or damage that occurred on September 11, 2001. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
