      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>To amend title 28, United States Code, to provide that a national of the United States may only bring a claim against a foreign state for an injury which was caused by international terrorism and which occurred on September 11, 2001, and for other purposes.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in House</billTextVersionName>
